  "path": "README.md",
  "content": "# Digital Clock - Multiple Time Zones\n\nA Python-based digital clock application that displays current time across multiple time zones with real-time updates.\n\n## Features\n\n✨ **Multiple Display Formats**\n- Simple format (clean and easy to read)\n- Detailed format (with timezone info and UTC offsets)\n- 7-segment display (retro digital look)\n\n🌍 **12 Time Zones**\n- UTC (Universal Time)\n- EST (Eastern Standard Time)\n- CST (Central Standard Time)\n- MST (Mountain Standard Time)\n- PST (Pacific Standard Time)\n- GMT (Greenwich Mean Time)\n- CET (Central European Time)\n- IST (Indian Standard Time)\n- JST (Japan Standard Time)\n- AEST (Australian Eastern Standard Time)\n- NZST (New Zealand Standard Time)\n- SGT (Singapore Time)\n\n⚙️ **Customizable**\n- Add/remove time zones from display\n- Real-time updates every second\n- Reset to default configuration\n\n## Requirements\n\n```bash\npip install pytz\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\npython digital_clock.py\n```\n\n## Main Menu Options\n\n1. **Simple Format** - Clean table showing time, date, and UTC offset\n2. **Detailed Format** - Comprehensive info for each timezone\n3. **7-Segment Format** - Retro digital clock display\n4. **View All Timezones** - List all 12 available time zones\n5. **Select Timezones** - Customize which zones to display\n6. **Exit** - Close the application\n\n## Examples\n\n### Simple Format\n```\n⏰ WORLD CLOCK - CURRENT TIME IN MULTIPLE TIME ZONES ⏰\n\n  UTC    │ 14:30:45 │ Tuesday, July 15, 2025          │ UTC00:00\n  EST    │ 10:30:45 │ Tuesday, July 15, 2025          │ UTC-04:00\n  PST    │ 07:30:45 │ Tuesday, July 15, 2025          │ UTC-07:00\n  GMT    │ 15:30:45 │ Tuesday, July 15, 2025          │ UTC+01:00\n  JST    │ 23:30:45 │ Wednesday, July 16, 2025        │ UTC+09:00\n```\n\n### Detailed Format\n```\n┌─ UTC (UTC) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n│ Time:        14:30:45 PM\n│ Date:        Tuesday, July 15, 2025\n│ UTC Offset:  UTC00:00\n│ Timezone:    UTC\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n┌─ EST (America/New_York) ───────────────────────────────────────────\n│ Time:        10:30:45 AM\n│ Date:        Tuesday, July 15, 2025\n│ UTC Offset:  UTC-04:00\n│ Timezone:    America/New_York\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Clone the repository:\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/newmaker124/digital-clock.git\ncd digital-clock\n```\n\n2. Install dependencies:\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\n3. Run the application:\n```bash\npython digital_clock.py\n```\n\n## Author\n\nCreated with ❤️ by Copilot\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - Feel free to use and modify!\n"}, {
